<subSubSection pageId="272" pageNumber="273" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="272.[151,1437,690,1113]" pageId="272" pageNumber="273">
REMARKS: 
<bibRefCitation author="Rondani, C." box="[267,487,942,968]" pageId="272" pageNumber="273" refId="ref369190" refString="Rondani, C. (1863) Diptera exotica revisa et annotata novis nonnullis descriptis. Eredi Soliani, Modena, 99 pp., 1 pl. [This is the separate that came out before the journal version with a different title, here as Rondani (1864 a)]." type="book" year="1863">Rondani (1863: 10)</bibRefCitation>
described both sexes of 
<taxonomicName box="[764,989,942,968]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Syrphus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="272" pageNumber="273" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vertebratus">
<emphasis box="[764,989,942,968]" italics="true" pageId="272" pageNumber="273">Syrphus vertebratus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
without specifying the exact 
<taxonomicName box="[1320,1406,942,968]" family="Number" pageId="272" pageNumber="26" rank="family">number</taxonomicName>
of specimens, but giving a single measurement of length, from material received from R.A. Philippi, to whom he attributed the species name. 
<bibRefCitation author="Costa, A." box="[520,711,1014,1040]" pageId="272" pageNumber="273" pagination="13 - 48" refId="ref348459" refString="Costa, A. (1866) Acquisti fatti durante l'anno 1863. Annuario del Museo Zoologico della Regia Universita di Napoli, 3, 13 - 48." type="journal article" year="1866">
<collectingRegion box="[520,584,1014,1040]" country="New Zealand" name="West Coast" pageId="272" pageNumber="273">Costa</collectingRegion>
(1866: 31)
</bibRefCitation>
listed a single MZUN specimen (as “ 
<taxonomicName authority="&quot; Phil. Rond." authorityName="Phil. Rond." class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Syrphus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="272" pageNumber="273" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vertebratus">
<emphasis box="[1138,1364,1014,1040]" italics="true" pageId="272" pageNumber="273">Syrphus vertebratus</emphasis>
” Phil. Rond.
</taxonomicName>
) numbered “649”. We found 
<specimenCount box="[606,754,1051,1077]" pageId="272" pageNumber="273" type="generic" typeStatus="syntypes">two syntypes</specimenCount>
in this study. 
<bibRefCitation author="Thompson, F. C. &amp; Thompson, B. J." box="[915,1334,1050,1076]" pageId="272" pageNumber="273" pagination="317 - 331" refId="ref376372" refString="Thompson, F. C. &amp; Thompson, B. J. (2007) A new Toxomerus species from Chile (Diptera: Syrphidae). Studia Dipterologica, 13 [2006], 317 - 331." type="journal article" year="2007">Thompson &amp; Thompson (2007: 329)</bibRefCitation>
wrongly stated that the types of 
<taxonomicName authority="Rondani" authorityName="Rondani" authorityYear="1863" box="[458,716,1086,1113]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Syrphus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="272" pageNumber="273" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vertebratus">
<emphasis box="[458,472,1087,1113]" italics="true" pageId="272" pageNumber="273">S</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[486,614,1086,1112]" italics="true" pageId="272" pageNumber="273">vertebratus</emphasis>
Rondani
</taxonomicName>
were lost.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
